Data Structures
Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
 CADCBuf_Config_tADCBuf Global configuration
 CADCBuf_Conversion_tAn ADCBuf_Conversion data structure is used with ADCBuf_convert(). It indicates which channel to perform the ADC conversion on, how many conversions to make, and where to put them. The arg variable is an user-definable argument which gets passed to the ADCBuf_Callback when the ADC driver is in ADCBuf_RETURN_MODE_CALLBACK
 CADCBuf_CQConf_tChirp Quality(CQ) configuration Parameters
 CADCBuf_dataFormat_tADC Buffer data format Parameters
 CADCBuf_FxnTable_tThe definition of an ADCBuf function table that contains the required set of functions to control a specific ADC driver implementation
 CADCBuf_HwCfg_tADCBUF Driver HW configuration
 CADCBuf_Params_tADC Parameters
 CADCBuf_RxChanConf_tADC Buffer RX channel configuration Parameters
 CADCBuf_rxTestPatternConf_tADC Buffer test pattern configuration Parameters
 CADCBuf_TestPatternConf_tADC Buffer test pattern configuration Parameters
 CADCBufMMWave_Object_tADCBufMMWave Object
